<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1893-12-04T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1893-12-04T00:00:00-05:00" n="136" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d136">
                    <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Gresham</persName> to Mr.
                                <persName type="to">Bayard</persName>.</hi></head>
                    <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                    <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department
                                    of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1893-12-04"><hi rend="italic">December 4,
                            1893</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                    <p>You will inform Lord Rosebery that, yielding to his desire, this Government
                        consents further negotiations for making the award of the Paris Tribunal
                        effective shall be conducted here with the British ambassador. While your
                        generous offer to visit Washington and aid us is appreciated, the President
                        will not impose the burden upon you.</p>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>